fields.description:
The RHEL and CentOS 6 installation instructions need to be updated to reflect Eucalyptus 3.1's new package set.  Both operating systems use the same instructions.

# Configure the Eucalyptus package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component:
{code}
yum install http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/6/x86_64/eucalyptus-release-3.1.noarch.rpm
{code}
# Configure the Euca2ools package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component or Euca2ools:
{code}
yum install http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/euca2ools/2.1/rhel/6/x86_64/euca2ools-release-2.1.noarch.rpm
{code}
# Configure the EPEL package repository on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component or Euca2ools:
{code}
yum install http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/6/x86_64/epel-release-6.noarch.rpm
{code}
# Configure the ELRepo repository on each host that will run Walrus:
{code}
yum install http://downloads.eucalyptus.com/software/eucalyptus/3.1/rhel/6/x86_64/elrepo-release-6.noarch.rpm
{code}
# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription you will have received a package that grants you access to VMware and SAN components.  If you wish to use either of these components, install this package on each host that will run a Eucalyptus component.  Otherwise, skip this step.
{code}
yum install eucalyptus-enterprise-release-3.1-1.noarch.rpm
{code}
# Install the Eucalyptus cloud controller software on each planned CLC host:
{code}
yum groupinstall eucalyptus-cloud-controller
{code}
# Install the Eucalyptus node controller software on each planned NC host.  Clouds that use the VMware hypervisor do not have NCs; if you plan to use VMware then skip this step.
{code}
yum install eucalyptus-nc
{code}
# Install the software for the remaining Eucalyptus components.  The following example shows most components being installed on the same host.  You can use different hosts for each component.
{code}
yum install eucalyptus-cc eucalyptus-sc eucalyptus-walrus
{code}
# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription and plan to use the VMware hypervisor, install the Eucalyptus VMware broker software on each CC host:
{code}
yum install eucalyptus-enterprise-vmware-broker
{code}
# If you have a Eucalyptus subscription and plan to use Eucalyptus's SAN capabilities, install the Eucalyptus SAN adapter software on each SC host:
{code}
yum install eucalyptus-enterprise-storage-san
{code}
# After you have installed Eucalyptus, test multicast connectivity between each CLC and Walrus, SC, and VMware broker host.
## Run the following receiver command on the CLC:
{code}
java -classpath /usr/share/eucalyptus/jgroups-2.11.1.Final.jar org.jgroups.tests.McastReceiverTest -mcast_addr 224.10.10.10 -port 5555
{code}
## Run the following sender command on each Walrus host:
{code}
java -classpath /usr/share/eucalyptus/jgroups-2.11.1.Final.jar org.jgroups.tests.McastSenderTest -mcast_addr 224.10.10.10 -port 5555
{code}
## Repeat the previous step on each SC host and VMware broker host
## If you are installing an HA environment, repeat these tasks with the second CLC.

Your installation is now complete.
